  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oil in a deep frying pan to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Knead kachori dough and divide into 4-6 pieces.",
    "Roll out each piece into a thin circle.",
    "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat.",
    "Add ghee or oil and cook lamb mince until browned, breaking it up with a spoon.",
    "Add onion, ginger, garlic, cumin, coriander, garam masala, and salt. Cook for 5 minutes.",
    "Brush kachori dough with water and place in the pan.",
    "Cook for 2-3 minutes or until kachori is golden brown.",
    "Flip kachori and cook for another 2 minutes.",
    "Drain on paper towels and serve hot with lamb filling."
